node.text:
Earlier this year @TannerVanVark hit the open road up the coast from LA with REAL Filmer @Fulton7 in his new acquired adventure mobile to explore a flatbar oasis called @TheRecDIY in Nipomo, CA and spend a couple days skating with the locals. 

We hope this inspires you to get out and skate somewhere new with your friends, or build something for the skaters in your local scene.

In the weeks following the filming of this video The Rec was torn out to make way for another shopping center. As a small Thank You to The Rec crew for their efforts Tanner donated $500 to their next project, wherever or whenever that may be.

Thanks to The Rec crew for letting us skate. Can’t wait to see what is next. Thanks for the good times!

node.title: Tanner Van Vark : The Rec DIY

node.text:
To celebrate the collection @oscarputdowntheknife made for us, @masonsilva wanted to hit some classic Natas spots around his hood. All the while we kept getting the feeling like Natas was watching around every turn... “was that him?”...

This on is special. Hope you like it.

node.text:
Originally this video was going to be a stand alone Robbie part, then Chima dropped a full part in our laps... fuck yeah, lets put them together and give everyone more to watch! The title 'From Here To There' felt really fitting with Robbie and Chima working on parts on either side of the globe that worked together as one piece.

Through skateboarding you'll meet and become friends with people from all walks of life and from every end of the world - sometimes you're lucky to be on the same team and travel that world together... Cheers on the hard work for this one @brockel, @chimaferguson 🍻

node.text:
Moments like these… ❤️

We told @HarryLintell that the lads at @FreeSkateMag wanted him to take a seat at @BlackSheepStore to film a little video of him looking through the newest issue of the mag hot off the presses… little did he know there was a surprise waiting for him on page 18… his first pro ad! The moment he saw it his friends and family ambushed him with his debut pro boards. His reaction was priceless, followed by a hug from Mum, and popped bottles 🍾 

Harry’s Pro Oval 8.28” & Plague Doctor 8.5” are making their way to skate shops soon including @blacksheepstore @510skateshop @focus_scotland @nocomplyatx @laborskateshop @nativeskate @slamcityskates @humiditynola @familiask8shop @idealbirmingham @cardiffskateboardclub @3rdlair @35thnorth @levelskateboards_ @boredofsouthsea @prestigeboise @venueskateboards @flavourskateshop @fiftyfiftystore @ftcsanfrancisco @sluggerskatestore @welcomeskatestore @thebossshop @atlasskateboarding @sessionarkaden @mammaskateshop @upriseskateshop @uselesswoodentoys @pawnshopskateco @labcph just to name a few…

All photos by @reeceleung

node.text:
HARRY IS PRO! 🍾

We thought there was no better way to surprise @harrylintell Harry with his well-deserved pro boards than in Manchester at @blacksheepstore, with his family and friends there to pour a pint or two over his head. Cheers Harry! 🍻

Keep an eye out for his boards are they make their way to shops in the coming weeks. Thank you to everyone who lent a hand in making this happen ❤️

node.text:
@HarryLintell gives @JenkemMag a tour around his hometown of Manchester, in Northern England - for a typical day meeting oddballs and skating a city that was built centuries before America was even a thought in anyone’s mind. Now playing on jenkemmag.com (link in our bio, duh). This one will brighten your day for sure!

🎥 : @victsiskre 🎬 : @alexiscastro

node.text:
@PatrickPraman : A REAL Short Part 🎞 now playing on @ThrasherMag IGTV

With music selection and editing by Patrick himself (with a little help from REAL Filmer @Fulton7), Patty puts his own personal style and finesse on everything in this short but extra sweet part - from the streets or in the editing seat. We hope it gets you stoked to go skate and get creative.

node.text:
“This one has my name on it?!”

That moment when going record shopping before the sesh turns into an amazing surprise for @masonsilva ❤️ swipe through to get a glimpse

A huge THANK YOU to @jawbreakerband for making these very special boards happen and to @soundsations_records for being so rad and helping surprise Mason!

Mason’s ‘Boxcar’ 8.5” is shipping to select skate shops now with more on the way soon!

Stay tuned in the coming weeks for details on the Limited Edition ‘Salt Girl’ boards - only 500 made - each will come with custom guitar pick - will be available for shops to order soon.

Photos: @morfordmedia
